---
title: Saucy Italian Chicken Wraps with Tomato-Scallion Relish
description: These wraps are a light and easy lunchtime treat filled with all the saucy Italian flavors we love. First you’ll warm fully cooked chicken with our aromatic Italian seasoning blend, scallions, and garlic in a quick, creamy sauce. You’ll load it all onto tortillas with a fresh, tangy tomato relish, roll ’em up, then quick-sear in a pan till golden brown and crisp. A sprinkle of scallion greens tops off this easy, fresh lunch idea.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/saucy-italian-chicken-wraps-d2d149bd.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/646465ff1880dc60f707abb3.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/saucy-italian-chicken-wraps-646465ff1880dc60f707abb3
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 500 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 42 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1020 mg
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Italian
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter
@lemon{1}. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%oz} dry with paper towels. Thinly slice
crosswise. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is warmed
through and scallion whites are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Use 2 tsp Italian seasoning for 4 servings; save remaining for another use.

Remove from heat; stir in @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, juice from one lemon wedge,
and 3 tbsp water (two lemon wedges and 6 tbsp water for 4 servings) until
melted and combined. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

> TIP: For saucier chicken, stir in another splash of water if needed.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, half the scallion greens, juice from one
lemon wedge (two lemon wedges for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Add saucy chicken and
tomato relish (draining first) to bottom third of each tortilla. Fold up bottom
side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward
filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add wraps and
cook until golden brown on all sides, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches,
> adding a drizzle of oil between batches and adjusting heat as needed.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates. Top with remaining scallion
greens and serve.